//- Rendering — the full render story on one tab. In reading order:
//- what the user saw (video player and/or filmstrip, or the
//- per-run screenshot gallery), then why rendering was delayed
//- (recalculate-style work and forced reflows before first paint from
//- the Chrome trace, the render-blocking requests from the HAR, and a
//- cross-link to the CPU tab when animations run on the main thread).
//-
//- The playback view degrades by configuration, never by file sniffing:
//-   video + filmstrip : player + transport + HUD + timeline + strip
//-   filmstrip only    : a large frame preview replaces the player,
//-                       frames/arrow keys drive it, play steps through
//-                       the frames, speed buttons and the download
//-                       link disappear
//-   video only        : player + timeline + HUD, no strip
//-   neither           : no player, preview, transport or strip at all —
//-                       the tab can still exist for the screenshots and
//-                       the why-was-rendering-delayed cards (page gating)
//-
